  subtitle="A dental bridge literally bridges the gap left by missing teeth. Fixed and natural-looking, a bridge restores your bite, prevents shifting, and gives you back a complete smile."
  heroImg={heroImg}
  overviewTitle="Close the gap. Restore your bite."
  overviewText="A dental bridge consists of one or more artificial teeth (pontics) held in place by crowns cemented onto the teeth on either side of the gap. The result is a fixed, non-removable restoration — you eat, speak, and smile with it just like natural teeth. Unlike a removable partial denture, a bridge doesn't come out, doesn't require adhesive, and provides a stable chewing surface. We also offer implant-supported bridges, which eliminate the need to modify adjacent healthy teeth altogether."
  overviewExtra="Patients from Bayside, Whitestone, Fresh Meadows, and Little Neck who are missing one or more teeth often turn to dental bridges as a faster, less invasive alternative to implants. At Thrive Dental, we fabricate all bridges using digital impressions from our iTero scanner — ensuring a fit precise enough that adjustments at delivery are minimal. Our all-porcelain bridges are shade-matched to your surrounding teeth so the restoration is visually seamless. If you're weighing a bridge vs. an implant, we'll give you an honest assessment of which is better suited to your anatomy, timeline, and budget — without pushing you toward the more expensive option if the bridge is the right call."
